<br>
I just wanted to say one or two things..  first, I have had success in the past petitioning to have a friend worldkicked, the GM responded to me in tells and kicked my friend.  Apparently either he could tell the guy was LD or he didn't care about procedure. =)  So try it, it might work, although with the switch to non-server specific gms I doubt it.<br>
<br>
As for 1018s though, the fastest way to get back in game is to completely exit everquest and reboot your computer.  If you are using a router, you may want to reboot the router too.  The reason as it was explained to me was that most computers when they make a connection to the internet through their ISP are at that time assigned an IP address for their computer (or router).  By rebooting and reconnecting, you get assigned a new IP address.  Everquest will notice that the IP it was trying to talk to before doesn't exist anymore, and it will drop the character on the next server synchronization, which usually happens every half hour or so.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps someone.  It might not be valid anymore if there is some new bug with 1018 errors, but worked beautifully in the past.<br>
<br>
Euphrates <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=terenne>Terenne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.slegion.org/avatars/alliertes.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/03 6:29:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25990.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: options</span><hr size=1> I've had a guildmate petition for a world-kick for me before, and the person who offered was in the guide program at the time, so it's not against policy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdlan>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 226<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/18/03 9:13:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25990.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-viatores.org/book1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: options</span><hr size=1> I've not only petitioned for a friend, and had friends petition for me, I've petitioned for myself while two boxing, and never been told that.<br>
